      • getScriptFailedThrowable

        public java.lang.Throwable getScriptFailedThrowable()
        Get the throwable of the inline script execution. Note that only internal errors are reported. Normal syntax errors will flow into the error stream of the script context which means that that this method returns in such a case a value of null - even when the script execution did fail.
        Returns:
        the throwable of the inline script execution, or null = no internal error
